A man has been arrested for repeatedly defiling his 13-year old daughter before before impregnating her. The 35-year old Ephram Kimani Macharia was arrested by detectives in Murang'a county. DCI Director George Kinoti said after the noticing the the condition of the class five pupil, the head teacher Gatumbi Primary School took the child to a local hospital, where she was confirmed to be six months pregnant. "Inquiry into the odious situation revealed that the father was responsible," Kinoti said. The girl narrated to the detectives that the man had been defiling her severally since July 2020. This was the period in which schools were closed due to coronavirus. The girl has since been put under the care of a children's officer at a rescue centre in Muthithi. The suspect is in custody as further investigations continue.